# ThreadSanitizer suppression file for the DNA messenger test suite.
#
# This file starts empty by design. Do NOT pre-populate with guessed
# suppressions from OpenSSL / libsodium / SQLCipher false positives.
# Populate only in response to concrete TSan output from a real run.
#
# Each suppression added here must carry a comment explaining:
#   1. The race pattern TSan reported (copy the TSan frame header).
#   2. Why it is benign (external library lazy init, etc.).
#   3. The date and the contributor who verified it.
#
# To run the concurrency tests under TSan, see messenger/docs/CONCURRENCY.md.
#
# Phase 2 introduced this file; see .planning/phases/02-concurrency-safety/.
